folder: Willow St. & Clark St., Brooklyn, NY
text:
100-104 Willow Street at the S.W. corner of Clark Street, showing the Peck House (No. 100 at the corner) which was demolished prior to 1908.
About 1906.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Willow St. & Clark St., Brooklyn, NY
text:
103-113 Willow Street, west side, near Clark Street. J. Warren Greene, a lawyer, lived in the frame house at the right. On the site of the partially seen apartment house at the extreme right, formerly stood
the home of William E. Harmon, Real estate dealer.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Willow St. & Clark St., Brooklyn, NY
text:
98-114 Willow Street, south from Clark Street, showing No. 98, at the extreme right. The frame house in the center, No. 104, was built in 1827
and is said to be the oldest house on Brooklyn Heights.
May 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Willow St. & Clark St., Brooklyn, NY
text:
Willow Street, east side, north from Clark Street. In the right foreground was the estate of Samuel Rowland. The homes were sold in 1925.
In 1929, an apartment building occupied the site.
1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Willow St. & Clark St., Brooklyn, NY
text:
Willow Street, south from Clark Street, which may be seen in the foreground. Partially seen at the right is No. 94, a six story apartment
house known as Willow Court.
August 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
